<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN"
    "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
  build/entitlements.plist
  Hardened-runtime entitlements for RAI Audio Analyzer v2.

  Only needed for Developer ID (notarized) signing.
  Ad-hoc signing (the default in build/build_macos.sh) does not require
  this file, but passing it to codesign is harmless.

  Developer ID usage:
    codesign -f -deep -o runtime
             -E build/entitlements.plist
             -s "Developer ID Application: Your Name (TEAMID)"
             "dist/RAI Audio Analyzer.app"

  Why these two entitlements:
  numba JIT-compiles Python to native code via LLVM (llvmlite).
  The hardened runtime blocks both capabilities by default.

  allow-jit: lets the process use MAP_JIT mmap, required by numba on
    Apple Silicon and macOS 10.14+ (W^X memory policy).

  allow-unsigned-executable-memory: lets the process write to executable
    memory pages not marked MAP_JIT (llvmlite fallback on some versions).

  No other entitlements (network, microphone, camera, etc.) are granted.
-->
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-jit</key>
    <true/>
    <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-unsigned-executable-memory</key>
    <true/>
</dict>
</plist>
